{
  "texts": [
    "Analogous calculations show that the partial equilibrium in this case readsf eq,w (t, A, w) = C(t, A)(1 -w) -1+ Āω ℓ +ε ν ℓ (1-µ ℓ) (1 + w) -1+ Āω ℓ +ε ν ℓ (1+µ ℓ),(23)and the previous remarks hold also for these equilibria, since they have the same structure of (22).",
    "Notice that the average opinion related to the distribution ( 23) is µ ℓ, which is in line with Conjecture 1.",
    "Additionally, ( 23) is well-defined as long as µ ℓ / = ±1, since in such cases we would obtain a Dirac delta (in Subsection 4.2 we will provide more details on this matter).At last, if we take into account both agent-agent and agent-leader interactions, we end up with a similar Beta distribution combining the dependencies on ρ Ā, m Ā and µ ℓ, namelyf eq,w (t, A, w) = C(t, A)(1 -w) -1+ λp( Āωp+ε)(ρ Ā(t)-m Ā(t))+λ ℓ ( Āω ℓ +ε)(1-µ ℓ) σ 2 p +σ 2 ℓ × (1 + w) -1+ λp( Āωp+ε)(ρ Ā(t)+m Ā(t))+λ ℓ ( Āω ℓ +ε)(1+µ ℓ) σ 2 p +σ 2 ℓ.",
    "(24)All previous considerations still hold in this general case.",
    "The function c was so chosen so that the area subtended by the graphs was equal to 1, but other choices would have been acceptable (and they would have led analogous results)."
  ]
